Two teenagers have been charged with attempted murder after a man was found with serious injuries in Nottinghamshire.Emergency services were called to a footpath near Jubilee Way South, in Mansfield,  at about 03:00 BST on Thursday. The man, in his 30s, remains in hospital in a serious condition. Nottinghamshire Police said the teenagers, 17 and 15, appeared at Nottingham Magistrates' Court on Saturday.
The boys were remanded into custody and will next appear at Nottingham Crown Court on 16 August.Police added a 19-year-old man, who was also arrested on suspicion of attempted murder, had been released on bail while investigations continued.Follow BBC Nottingham on Facebook, on X, or on Instagram. Send your story ideas to eastmidsnews@bbc.co.uk or via WhatsApp on 0808 100 2210.
